CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 8, 1960, pg. 2, reads: "Tragic Picture - The tragedy which began in a Mississippi college, with the acute homesickness of a 15-year-old Pittsburgher and ended when the youth, in a stolen car, was shot dead by a Memphis policeman, is etched in this picture which shows the boy's father, Maurice W. Baylor of 1845 Bedford Ave., holding the dog of his son - an only child. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Maurice W. Baylor holding puppy in front of armoire, with Squirt pinup calendar in background, 1845 Bedford Avenue, Hill District
